race.comment: ZIPPER BANK (4) was well off top last time, finishing 6th (23.10) in a Grade 5 at Maitland. Has never missed the frame here at the trip including one win. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from three starts. Can make amends. CLEO'S A CHANCE (1) has a strong record this journey here with five wins and a minor from nine starts. In the money last time at Taree Super Track (17.55) in a NG, finishing a 4 length third. Looks well placed here and among the chances. OUR CHINA RED (3) was big odds last time but gave a huge sight after a fast early split, weakening late to finish a 2.5 lengths fourth (22.77) over 400m at Maitland. The form from his last run stacks up well. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. ROSY LONE (2) gets a chance to redeem an unplaced effort here last start.
